    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\na1542b091dd7b919fa8524c1c909ef897dde9299\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom source\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n```\r\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal win = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf, true, {\r\n  relative = 'editor',\r\n  row = 5, col = 5,\r\n  width = 10, height = 10,\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_config(win, {\r\n  width = 3, height = 3,\r\n  row = 10, col = 10, -- Runs fine without this line,\r\n                      -- this line gives:\r\n--[[\r\n\r\nE5113: Error while calling lua chunk: mwe.lua:8: non-float cannot have 'row'\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_win_set_config'\r\n        mwe.lua:8: in main chunk\r\n\r\n--]]\r\n  -- relative = 'editor', -- Adding this fixes it.\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nYou shouldn't have to re-specify `relative` -- the `nvim_win_set_config` docs state that existing config options will be kept:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"656\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5308024/166261454-db88693f-57ed-4ada-b824-4b6e5b3eb25c.png\">\r\n\r\nSee: `parse_float_config` in `win_config.c`.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nYou can't set `row`/`col` without re-specifying `relative`.",
